<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Museums     08-13 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Museums,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Minister Breaks Tradition, Orders Museums Open On Holiday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Breaking a revered Italian custom, the culture
minister has ordered state-run museums to remain open on August 15,
a national holiday.
   In past years tourists have had to put up with almost everything
in Italy being shut down on the national holiday, called
``Ferragosto.''
   The new culture minister, Ferdinando Facchiano, said the museums
should stay open so foreign tourists and others could enjoy Italy's
art.
   However, one of Italy's most famous museums, the Uffizi Gallery
in Florence, may be closed. Its employees have threatened to strike
from Monday to Wednesday, saying the work order violates an
agreement on opening hours on holidays.
</TEXT>
